comments: Professor Taormina was very helpful with the material. She is a very beautiful looking woman.

SHE IS THE BEST MATH TEACHER YOU WILL EVER HAVE HANDS DOWN!!!! She was very helpful. I am the kind of person who never does well in math, I used to get 60\'s. I got high grades in her class and came out with an A! She is the best, so clear and easy to understand! MUST TAKE HER! You will love math after her class!!!!

PROS:Has great knowledge about Java. Somewhat of a sweet personality. CONS:If u ask her 2many times something she will get frustrated and snap at u. Strict bout due dates if ur absent g.luck on getting the handouts. Spends the 1st 3 weeks drilling the idea of pair programming just 2 tell u at the end of the semester dat you should work on your own.
Also, she drops the lowest grade you get, replaces it with your Final grade if you do well, and she gives out bonuses.

This class and subject is hard. I don\'t care how good you are at math. Yes the homework online is graded, and attendance is mandatory, but if you actually show that you are trying, she will help you out. Graded homework actually boosted up my grade to passing. The notes she gives do help out and she is clear on how to do the steps.

She should prob not be teaching precalc. i am good at math and she confused me. web hw(20% of the grade) took up way too much time that i needed for other classes and it made me ignore the daily hw that she doesnt go over anyway. tests are looong and hard. 5 people actually lasted to the final. she is dedicated but not great at actually teaching.

Teacher talks during the class all the time. Doesnt understand that we have classes besides her. Gves us online hw that mandartory and what online hw isnt want we learn in her class at all. Very boring and suggest you take other teacher for pre calculus

The sweetest professor ever!! She is so helpful and understanding. Her work is very easy you just have to make sure you study. for her online class she allows you to bring in notes for the midterm and final. She gives good lectures and homework. She\'s by far one of the most sweetest professor at Nassau.
Amazing!!!! The world needs teachers like her! I\'m taking her online class, and I\'m the worst at math but she makes it so interesting. Very sweet and helpful! So understanding! Love her!!!

SHE\'S AMAZING ! she\'s extremely helpful and super nice. she posts her lectures on blackboard so if you miss class you\'re notes are RIGHT THERE.her tests are very fair and she drops your lowest test grade if you do well on the final.
Great notes, very helpful, if you pay attention and do the work its hard to fail her class.

shes a really great teacher. she teaches it, makes a youtube video on it, has lab once a week which is kinda like a quiz thats not graded that goes over everything all week, shes very lenient shes awesome. and if your not good at math she is the teacher to pick

She is extremely professional and organized. Her lectures are on PowerPoint and video-taped on YouTube. She also has plenty of office hours. There is no reason for anyone to do badly if they put in the required work.

Well im awful at math and didnt do so well but professor Taormina was a nice person and is EXTREMELY dedicated to her work as a math prof. She posts youtube videos of her to help you and is always available when you need her for help. Her class is kind of hard if you dont like math but she will give you every opportunity to succeed. She\'s GREAT! :)
She makes everything easy to understand. Three tests and a final, and if the final is higher than your lowest test grade, the final replaces it. Easy online homeworks. If you need help, just ask.
An excellent teacher.
amazing teacher, so understanding and really helps every student learn. She\'s greattttt i love herrr
A gud prof..knws how to teach..sweet and nice..highly recommended to anyone..she will try her best to help..knw the stuff well..love this prof(:
A gud prof..knws how to teach..sweet and nice..higly recommended..

If I have any problem understanding something my professor taught in statistics, I go to her for help. I know I will leave her with my problems solved. She is great I wouldn\'t go to any other person for help.
